<exercise id="fs-idm231745792">
<problem id="fs-idm242781984">
<para id="fs-idm251626048">What is different about the “siege and defence of” Fort Mifflin? According to Martin, why is this victory not as widely publicized and celebrated as some other battles?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm254473600">
<problem id="fs-idm232016640">
<para id="fs-idm258235520">Why does Martin steal from the home in Milltown?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm250396640">
<problem id="fs-idm231302192">
<para id="fs-idm243360208">What was dangerous about Martin’s actions in Milltown or Mount Holly?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm232762656">
<problem id="fs-idm232047520">
<para id="fs-idm205060032">What factors make Martin’s travel especially difficult?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm239483456">
<problem id="fs-idm249571472">
<para id="fs-idm232535968">Explain Martin’s reference to a “continual lent.”</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm232114576">
<problem id="fs-idm250466240">
<para id="fs-idm260507296">Martin notes that soldiers were in “excellent fighting trim, as [they] were starved and as cross and ill-natured as curs.” Explain what he means by this statement.</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm235931504">
<problem id="fs-idm255360592">
<para id="fs-idm239988320">To what extent were you surprised to see what Congress sent to the soldiers for their Thanksgiving meal? Why does Martin say the donation would “make the world stare”?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm256878416">
<problem id="fs-idm247700576">
<para id="fs-idm254995072">Why does Martin say that the soldiers were naked?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm214970048">
<problem id="fs-idm246570096">
<para id="fs-idm259093440">What keeps Martin from considering dispersion?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm206441904">
<problem id="fs-idm249272944">
<para id="fs-idm258144176">What does Martin think of the way the Congress is providing for the Continental Army?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
